This was another session I thought was going to have to go on hold for a while but today’s outdoor cake smash was so much fun. Check out my stories for some more images. I combined this with some family shots first and shots of this gorgeous little man by himself and I’m so excited. For now - these sessions are going to be photographed outdoor - socially distances and shot on my 70-200 lens to give us tons of space to stay apart. I have a new set of procedures in place to ensure we all stay safe. I have a few sessions that were put on hold during lockdown to book in but if you would like one of these sessions - please do get in touch for more info! Thankyou. How cute is this little chap!’ Xx

Outdoor newborn photography. I have to confess - back in March I did not think the future for my business looked bright. I really saw no return to “ business as usual”. As you will know if you follow along with my madness on here - I didn’t find lockdown easy. Emotions were all over the place and even now - just yesterday - I welled up in Marks & Spencer - just with sadness for a life that is no longer the same. ( don’t worry. I am still my very cheerful happy self but sometimes it’s just a bit overwhelming do you think?) But after some weeks - I picked myself up - I dusted myself down and I looked at a list full of shoots with thick pencil lines through saying - “no longer possible” and I started to think around the issues we face. A new set of COVID-19 procedures in place - I went out on our first day that we were told we could go back to work and I tried this. I met this beautiful little lady and her wonderful mum and dad and took lovely images to capture her while she is still so young. I have lots more to edit but for now. Meet F - 4 weeks and 3 days worth of gorgeous little lady She had been in my diary for months and I am so very glad I got to capture her at this young stage xx

Long used @goustocooking - over a year now and it’s definitely been a life saver. I have a blog and I’ll try and put this up later for anyone interested although I’m not sure your open for new clients again yet ? Anyway. This is an excellent addition to their responsible packaging and it has the double benefit of being able to reuse it to drop off our food donations to the local animal charity. Anyway. Wanted to tell everyone as it’s great to see companies doing what they can to lessen plastic waste. @goustocooking #reducereuserecycle #stayhome #stayhomestaysafe #covid19 #documentaryphotography #3b&me #3boysandmephotography #documentyourdays #snaphappybritmums #documentinglockdown #documentinglockdowninlondon #lifeduringlockdown #shotoniphone

Have started to see agencies and retailers looking for photographers with their own children to help shoot AW due to the current situation. Have put this together and will put more or Jackson’s photos in my stories today. Please do get in touch if we can help. Modelling portfolio gallery link in the bio. Nina and jack xxxxx

Hello! I hope everyone is safe and well and beginning to slowly find we can do a few more things than we could. I am gearing up to start back to work, as soon as government guidelines allow. At this point, it looks like it will be early June. If your shoots had to go on hold, I will be contacting you by email over the coming week. After that, I’ll be looking at booking in dates for my lavender shoots. Whilst nothing is certain at this point, I am hopeful these will be able to go ahead, and I plan to offer extra evenings at the farm, if the availability is there. With the way the world has changed, as a predominately outdoor photographer, I’m in the fortunate position of only having to implement a few new practices to ensure that you and me stay safe, and always at a 2 meter distance. I am putting together new, shorter outdoor family sessions too, along with clear guidance for the way my shoots will run. I’ve really missed you all, I am not ashamed to say that I felt a bit sad coming to terms with not being able to walk next to you and your family while I work, chatting along the way, and

Charles Warner | The Union Times A good father is the greatest man in a child’s life, and that’s why we have Father’s Day, the day set aside to honor and celebrate fathers. Yet even as we celebrate our fathers on Father’s Day, we should not forget to celebrate God, our Heavenly Father. God is our creator and each and every human being is made in His image, a distinction that makes the human race unique in nature. Not only did He create us, He did something no other father would ever do, He allowed His son die for the sins of all humanity, taking them upon Him and taking upon Himself the punishment due the human race. By doing what no other father would do or would be expected to do, God, our Heavenly Father, gave us all the chance at life everlasting with Him and Christ in Heaven. Our fathers play their part in giving us life and caring for us as we grow up, and we, their children, owe them a debt of gratitude we can never truly repay and so it is right that we honor them, not just on Father’s Day, but throughout the year. At the same time, we all owe God a debt we can never even come close to repaying and so it is even more right what remember and honor Him throughout our lives for giving us life in His image; giving us His son so that we might be forgiven our sins and enjoy eternal life; and giving us good fathers who, striving to act as God would want them to, work their every waking minute to support, care, nurture, and love their families. Happy Father’s Day !
